    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311F1 Advisory Committee/1061</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Netherland Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 152</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Netherlands Minister presents his compliments to the Honorable the Secretary
                    of State and has the honor to acknowledge receipt of the note of November 7th
                    regarding the Wheat Meeting. In this note, the Honorable the Secretary of State
                    informed Dr. Loudon that the request of the Government of the Netherlands to be
                    represented at the meetings of the Wheat Conference by an observer could not be
                    complied with.</p>
                <p>Her Majesty’s Government has been informed of this decision. The United States
                    Government will understand that the Government of the Netherlands, under these
                    circumstances, has to make all reservations as regards any decisions taken
                    without consultation of the Netherlands Government in connection with the
                    post-war wheat trade.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-14">November 14,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
